New Node Package

1. Create directory
2. npm init -> Create package.json
3. Create start file (index.js)
4. Create "lib" and "test" folders
5. Create .gitignore file -> 'touch .gitignore' (https://github.com/github/gitignore)


Node Project
1. Clone or Create(steps above)
2. 'npm install'


NPM Homework

npm init
npm search partialPackageName
npm install (npm i) --save --save-dev
npm install -g
npm update --save --save-dev
npm uninstall (remove) --save --save-dev
npm link (develop packages locally, inside package directory) 
npm link packageName (install linked package outside of development directory) 
npm publish (publish to npmjs)

**Advanced Mode
npm add-user
npm outdated
npm start / stop (setup in package.json)

package.json
{
	"dependencies": {
		"lodash": "^0.0.1" vs "~0.0.1" vs "0.0.1"
	}	
}


Require Hints
require('lodash') [npm installed]

Inside of the project, require() to access module.exports
require('./lib') [lib/index.js]
require('./lib/hello') [lib/hello.js]

Inside of Directory: [test/index.js]
require('../') [index.js]
require('../lib/hello') [lib/hello.js]
